pull_request.title: Bump csv-parse from 3.1.3 to 4.4.6
pull_request.body:
Bumps [csv-parse](https://github.com/wdavidw/node-csv-parse) from 3.1.3 to 4.4.6.
Changelog *Sourced from [csv-parse's changelog](https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv-parse/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md).* > ## Version 4.4.6 > > * security: remove regexp vulnerable to DOS in cast option, npm report 69742 > > ## Version 4.4.5 > > * ts: add buffer as allowed type for input, fix [#248](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/wdavidw/node-csv-parse/issues/248) > > ## Version 4.4.4 > > * package: latest dependencies > * bom: detection when buffer smaller than bom > * package: remove deprecated @types/should dependency > * package: update file path > > ## Version 4.4.3 > > * package: fix files declaration > > ## Version 4.4.2 > > * bom: parsing for BOM character [#239](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/wdavidw/node-csv-parse/issues/239) > * ts: add sync definition > * package: replace npm ignore with file field > > ## Version 4.4.1 > > Fix: > * columns: allows returning an array of string, undefined, null or false > > ## Version 4.4.0 > > New features: > * options: new bom option > > ## Version 4.3.4 > > * columns: enrich error message when provided as literal object > * cast: handle undefined columns > * skip_lines_with_error: new sample > > ## Version 4.3.3 > > Fix: > columns: fix es5 generation > > ## Version 4.3.2 > > Fix: > * columns: immutable option > ... (truncated)
Commits - [`fe3fe58`](https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv-parse/commit/fe3fe58e93f028889e7c0c609c06938073723d1d) Bump to version 4.4.6 - [`b9d3594`](https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv-parse/commit/b9d35940c6815cdf1dfd6b21857a1f6d0fd51e4a) security: remove regexp vulnerable to DOS in cast option, npm report 69742 - [`76d96e1`](https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv-parse/commit/76d96e16b166f745bcb137f0535724f4d3584f1c) Bump to version 4.4.5 - [`fecf171`](https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv-parse/commit/fecf1719cacf4e579f81d66054418284320d6e36) ts: add buffer as allowed type for input, fix [#248](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/wdavidw/node-csv-parse/issues/248) - [`9c53199`](https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv-parse/commit/9c531992ddeb24a09e5086629c185a0b0ae4cde3) fix: add buffer as allowed type for input - [`53ff6e7`](https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv-parse/commit/53ff6e7255efb7951adb26be66bb144105fa68e0) Bump to version 4.4.4 - [`7693582`](https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv-parse/commit/76935823d03933b4b98e6517773b71316aaa65b1) package: latest dependencies - [`620125e`](https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv-parse/commit/620125eb7eab55589903f0349666b36fb2772818) fix: Detecting BOM when data is not enough - [`c28279e`](https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv-parse/commit/c28279e5063f07ca8aefb2bc3199939401544c6b) package: update file path - [`30c11a2`](https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv-parse/commit/30c11a21503193d230cdda69b0a40a5df40728b0) Bump to version 4.4.3 - Additional commits viewable in [compare view](https://github.com/wdavidw/node-csv-parse/compare/v3.1.3...v4.4.6)

issue.title: Fix const issues in data grabbers
issue.body:
In /source/data/ we have many files that grab picnic table data. In some of these files, we use **const** variables instead of **let** variables. That doesn't really make sense for every variable. Some of them should be **let**. If you [understand the difference between const and let](https://tylermcginnis.com/var-let-const/), unlike us, please help us fix our scripts!

Example of a script with const issues:
https://github.com/earthiverse/picknic/blob/master/source/data/CA/AB/Airdrie_PicnicTables.ts

comment.body: I've sent over Canada, let me know if this is what you are looking for. Technically your const should work in those scenarios. However, Let would allow for manipulation of the data fields later. Let me know!
